begin_memory_text: We got to know each other a bit and talked about where we were from and what college we went to and the COVID situations going on at our colleges.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my experiences in Army ROTC and the month-long training that I had to do over the summer. We also talked a bit about our experiences being RA's.
end_memory_text: We kept talking about ROTC and also about being gay in the military since we were both LGBT. That led to us talking about our parent's reactions and if we were fully out.
rest_of_day_open: I do not see it going very well, since I have a lot of stuff to do for school and an upcoming three-day event for ROTC that I do not actually want to go to. I'm also a bit stressed out dealing with other people at my college and the whole COVID situation.
critical_positive: I think we had a good amount in common that let us have a good conversation without getting bored of each other's company. I also think we had a pretty good banter going and it made for a very enjoyable conversation. My partner was also very nice and easy to talk to.
critical_negative: I think our conversation worked really well and I wouldn't say that we had and problems that made the conversation boring or feel too long. I was afraid I was talking a bit too much, but I don't think it was bad enough that the entire conversation was ruined because of it.

begin_memory_text: I was kinda worried cause he said he was in the military and I am anti military, so I was nervous
middle_memory_text: We talked about RA life and how fucked up it is
end_memory_text: We talked about his intense military camping "trip" and how tragic that was
rest_of_day_open: I think I am just going to finish up some homework assignment. I also have some essays and projects due, but I think it'll be a good week and I am going to visit some friends and drink with them, so I am super excited about visiting  them this weekend
critical_positive: I am really glad that he told me he was gay. I was very nervous because you never know who you are going to meet on these chats and he pulled up in a cameo hat, and that is usually not a good sign, but I think he knew that and tried to make me feel as comfortable as possible and I really liked that.
critical_negative: I think if I had been a little bit more opened minded, then the beginning of the convo would have been more comfortable. I also assumed he had a good relationship with his parents and it turned out he didn't so just remembering to not make as many judgements about people.
